# Deploy to:   /etc/aide/aide.conf.d/99-hardening  (append to hardening baseline)
# Apply:       aide --init --config /etc/aide/aide.conf && mv /var/lib/aide/aide.db.new /var/lib/aide/aide.db
# Module:      file-transfer
# Requires:    hardening/self-managed/configs/aide/99-hardening applied first
#
# Extends AIDE scope to cover the SFTP chroot root. Excludes uploads/ to avoid
# false positives from expected transfer activity.
# Parameters modified from baseline:  none — additive only
#
# Note:        Baseline must be regenerated after appending — the current SFTP
#              directory structure becomes the new trusted state.

# ── SFTP — file-transfer ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/srv/sftp/sftpuser    OwnerMode
!/srv/sftp/sftpuser/uploads